            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "> **File Path:** `/root/Documents/Oscar GC/Commercial/S32-810479 Sprint 30 — Pemberton RFQ pack + redline c03/07-rfp-questionnaire.docx`\n\n# RFP Questionnaire\n\nPemberton Engineering Ltd. — Indirect MRO Framework — 3-Year Term\n\n**Document 07 of 7 — Bidder to complete and return**\n\n**Pemberton ref:** PEL/PROC/2026-RFQ-073 **Issued:** 11 May 2026 **Return by:** 23:59 BST, Friday 19 June 2026\n\nBidders shall complete every section. Where a question requires evidence, attach supporting documents to the bid response with cross-reference. Incomplete responses may be deemed non-compliant.\n\n# Section A — Company Information\n\nA1. Legal name and registered office. > ……………\n\nA2. Companies House (or equivalent) registered number. > ……………\n\nA3. VAT registration number. > ……………\n\nA4. Ultimate parent (if any) and group structure (one-line summary). > ……………\n\nA5. Names of Directors and Company Secretary. > ……………\n\nA6. Auditor of record and audit opinion category for the most recent three (3) financial years. > ……………\n\n# Section B — Financial Standing\n\nB1. Audited turnover, EBITDA, profit before tax, and net assets for the most recent three (3) financial years. > ……………\n\nB2. Has the Bidder been the subject of any County Court Judgment, winding-up petition, or insolvency proceeding in the last five (5) years? > ……………\n\nB3. Provide two (2) trade references and one (1) bank reference. > ……………\n\nB4. Confirm whether the Bidder is reliant on the framework for more than twenty percent (20%) of forecast revenue. > ……………\n\n# Section C — Operational Capability\n\nC1. Describe the Bidder’s national distribution network — number of distribution centres, geographic coverage, and any EU presence. > ……………\n\nC2. Average daily order volumes processed across the network. > ……………\n\nC3. Describe the Bidder’s e-procurement and EDI capability. > ……………\n\nC4. Provide three (3) reference accounts of comparable scale (≥£10m annual spend, multi-site MRO supply, 3+ years contract length). > ……………\n\nC5. Describe the Bidder’s emergency / 24×7 break-fix response capability. > ……………\n\n# Section D — Compliance and ESG\n\nD1. Confirm acceptance of the Compliance and ESG Annex (Document 06) in full. State any exceptions. > ……………\n\nD2. Provide the Bidder’s most recent modern slavery statement. > ……………\n\nD3. Confirm Bidder maintains “adequate procedures” within the meaning of section 7 of the Bribery Act 2010 and describe its anti-bribery training cadence. > ……………\n\nD4. Provide evidence of ISO 14001 certification (or equivalent). > ……………\n\nD5. Provide Bidder’s net-zero target status — published commitment, target date, SBTi validation status. > ……………\n\nD6. Provide Bidder’s most recent Scope 1+2 emissions disclosure. > ……………\n\nD7. Confirm Bidder’s cyber-security posture meets the requirements of clause 8 of the Compliance Annex. Attach Cyber Essentials Plus certificate or equivalent. > ……………\n\n# Section E — Commercial Position\n\nE1. Confirm acceptance of the Pricing Schedule (Document 03) rebate ladder, or propose alternative. > ……………\n\nE2. Confirm acceptance of MSA clause 6.2 (90-day payment terms) or propose alternative. > ……………\n\nE3. Confirm acceptance of MSA clause 5.4 (price benchmarking) and the most-favoured-customer clause in the Pricing Schedule (clause 7). > ……………\n\nE4. Identify any value-engineering or cost-out opportunities the Bidder has identified during bid preparation. > ……………\n\n# Section F — Contractual Position\n\nF1. Provide the Bidder’s redlined Master Supply Agreement (Document 02) attached to the bid response. **Bids submitted without a redlined MSA will be deemed non-compliant.**\n\nF2. List all material exceptions taken to the GTCs (Document 05). For each, identify the clause, the proposed alternative wording, and the rationale. > ……………\n\nF3. Confirm acceptance of the Compliance and ESG Annex (Document 06) without amendment, or state exceptions. > ……………\n\nF4. Confirm acceptance of the SLA (Document 04) targets, including all SLA penalties and the material-breach triggers in clause 5. > ……………\n\n# Section G — Transition\n\nG1. Describe the Bidder’s proposed transition plan from incumbent suppliers, with milestones and Buyer-side dependencies, on the assumption of contract signature by 30 September 2026 and Effective Date of 1 January 2027. > ……………\n\nG2. Identify any incumbent-supplier-held data, configurations, or assets that the Bidder considers necessary for transition. > ……………\n\n# Section H — Sustainability and Continuous Improvement\n\nH1. Identify four (4) productivity / cost-out / sustainability initiatives the Bidder commits to deliver in the first year of the Term, with quantified benefit estimates. > ……………\n\nH2. Describe the Bidder’s approach to packaging reduction, reusable packaging, and end-of-life take-back. > ……………\n\nH3. Identify any low-carbon, recycled-content, or remanufactured product lines the Bidder offers that are relevant to the Categories. > ……………\n\n**Bidder declaration**\n\nI, [Director Name], a Director of [Bidder Name], confirm that the responses set out above are true and accurate to the best of my knowledge and belief and are made on behalf of [Bidder Name].\n\nSigned: …………… Date: …………… Position: ……………\n\n---\n## Footnotes"
              }
            ],
